    "Periodically Change": "Changing the passwords you create for your various accounts can give you the assurance that you are taking all the necessary steps to keep your accounts and data secure.",
    "Password Strength": "Password strength checkers like LastPass allow people to verify the effectiveness of the passwords they create.",
    "Reliability": "Password managers are a great tool for people who have trouble understanding and organizing their passwords.",
    "Variety": "Accounts that have complex passwords that include many numbers, letters, and characters are less likely to be accessed by hackers.",
    "Avoid Wi-Fi": "Using public Wi-Fi without a VPN can allow hackers to track your online presence and potentially expose data on your device, including saved credentials.",
    "Never share password ": "Sharing your passwords with friends or family puts the cybersecurity of your personal accounts at risk.",
    "priority": "The longer your password is, the harder it is for hackers to guess it.",
    "Don't use personal Info": "Using personal information such as name, date of birth, address, or phone number in a password can compromise its effectiveness against cyber attacks.",
    "Randomize": "Yapping random patterns and sequences of letters, numbers, and characters in a password can help protect against password spraying attacks.",
    "Never reuse pass": "Reusing old passwords puts your accounts at risk of cyber attacks."
